---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Cigna Global in Singapore', level: 2 },
  { id: 'singapore-network', text: 'Network Coverage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'vs-local-options', text: 'vs Local Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose Cigna', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Singapore', href: '/countries/singapore/insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna vs Allianz', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-allianz-care' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'sgPrice', header: 'Singapore (Age 40)' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Silver', coverage: 'Inpatient + Day-patient', sgPrice: '$160-220/mo' },
  { plan: 'Gold', coverage: 'Silver + Outpatient', sgPrice: '$220-300/mo' },
  { plan: 'Platinum', coverage: 'Gold + Enhanced', sgPrice: '$300-400/mo' },
];

const hospitalColumns = [
  { key: 'type', header: 'Type' },
  { key: 'hospitals', header: 'Network Hospitals' },
  { key: 'directBilling', header: 'Direct Billing' },
];

const hospitalRows = [
  { type: 'Private', hospitals: 'Mount Elizabeth, Raffles Hospital, Gleneagles, Thomson Medical', directBilling: true },
  { type: 'Restructured', hospitals: 'Singapore General Hospital, National University Hospital, Tan Tock Seng', directBilling: true },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna Global Health Insurance in Singapore"
  description="Complete guide to using Cigna Global in Singapore. Local network coverage, pricing, and comparison to Integrated Shield Plans."
  headline="Cigna Global Health Insurance in Singapore"
  subheadline="Is Cigna Global the right choice for expats in Singapore? Coverage, pricing, and local options compared."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/singapore-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a Cigna Singapore Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Cigna Global in Singapore</h2>
  <p>
    Cigna Global is one of the most popular international insurers among Singapore expats. With high coverage limits, direct billing at major hospitals, and worldwide portability, it's a strong choice for those who want comprehensive protection in Singapore's expensive healthcare environment.
  </p>
  <p>
    Singapore's high healthcare costs make Cigna's $1-3M coverage limits valuable—a single hospital stay can easily exceed S$100,000.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$1-3M</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Annual coverage limits</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">1.5M+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Providers worldwide</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">24/7</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Multilingual support</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Singapore-Specific Quote"
    description="See what Cigna Global costs for expats living in Singapore."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/cigna-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="singapore-network">Network Coverage in Singapore</h2>
  <p>
    Cigna Global has excellent coverage in Singapore, with direct billing at both private and restructured hospitals.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={hospitalColumns} rows={hospitalRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Key Network Points</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Private hospitals:</strong> Mount Elizabeth, Raffles, Gleneagles, and other premium facilities</li>
    <li><strong>Restructured hospitals:</strong> SGH, NUH, TTSH—excellent care at lower costs</li>
    <li><strong>Direct billing:</strong> Cashless treatment at most major facilities</li>
    <li><strong>Specialists:</strong> Access to Singapore's world-class specialists</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Which Plan for Singapore?</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Silver:</strong> Inpatient only. Good if you pay routine care out of pocket (manageable in Singapore).</li>
    <li><strong>Gold:</strong> Practical choice. Full coverage including outpatient visits.</li>
    <li><strong>Platinum:</strong> Maximum coverage with enhanced mental health and wellness.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Deductible Strategy</h3>
  <p>
    Given Singapore's high costs, moderate deductibles ($1,000-2,500) balance premium savings with financial protection.
  </p>

  <h2 id="vs-local-options">vs Local Options</h2>
  <p>
    How does Cigna compare to local options?
  </p>

  <h3>Cigna Global vs Integrated Shield Plans</h3>
  <p>
    ISPs are only for Singapore citizens and PRs. If you're an expat without PR status, Cigna Global is one of your best options. If you're a PR, ISPs are very cost-effective but only cover Singapore care.
  </p>

  <h3>Choose Cigna Global If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>You're not a Singapore PR</li>
    <li>You want worldwide coverage</li>
    <li>Portability matters (may relocate)</li>
    <li>You want higher coverage limits</li>
    <li>Mental health coverage is important</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Consider Local/ISPs If:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>You're a Singapore PR</li>
    <li>You're staying in Singapore permanently</li>
    <li>Budget is the primary concern</li>
    <li>You don't need worldwide coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose Cigna in Singapore</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>Expats without PR status</li>
        <li>Those who travel frequently</li>
        <li>Families needing comprehensive coverage</li>
        <li>People who may relocate from Singapore</li>
        <li>Those wanting highest coverage limits</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Singapore PRs (consider ISPs)</li>
        <li>Budget-conscious expats</li>
        <li>Those with excellent employer coverage</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready for Coverage in Singapore?"
    description="Get a personalized Cigna Global quote for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/cigna-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Verify coverage details directly with Cigna before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
